  MythStory(
    id: 'hindu-kurukshetra',
    mythology: 'Hindu',
    icon: '⚔️',
    imageUrl: 'assets/images/Hindu/History/kurukshetra.webp',
    title: 'Perang Kurukshetra',
    titleEn: 'The Kurukshetra War',
    summary: 'Perang delapan belas hari antara Pandawa dan Korawa merenggut hampir seluruh generasi ksatria, termasuk Bhishma, Drona, Karna, dan Duryodhana, sebelum berakhir dengan kemenangan Pandawa.',
    summaryEn: 'The eighteen-day war between the Pandavas and Kauravas claims nearly an entire generation of warriors, including Bhishma, Drona, Karna, and Duryodhana, before ending in Pandava victory.',
    timeline: 'Mahabharata · Zaman Dvapara',
    timelineEn: 'Mahabharata · Dvapara Yuga',
    chapters: [
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Latar Belakang',
        headingEn: 'Background',
        body: '''Setelah masa pengasingan tiga belas tahun Pandawa berakhir, Duryodhana menolak mengembalikan meski hanya lima desa kecil sebagai kompromi damai, bersikeras tak akan menyerahkan tanah seluas ujung jarum tanpa perang. Krishna sendiri berangkat sebagai utusan damai ke Hastinapura, memohon perdamaian demi menghindari pertumpahan darah antar-keluarga, namun ditolak mentah-mentah dan bahkan nyaris ditangkap oleh Duryodhana yang murka. Dengan segala jalan damai buntu, kedua belah pihak mengumpulkan sekutu dari seluruh penjuru Bharatavarsha; Korawa menghimpun sebelas divisi tentara raksasa (akshauhini), sementara Pandawa hanya memiliki tujuh, namun diperkuat kehadiran Krishna sebagai penasihat dan kusir Arjuna. Kedua pasukan akhirnya berkemah berhadapan di padang Kurukshetra, tanah suci yang dipilih karena dianggap netral, menjelang perang delapan belas hari yang akan mengguncang seluruh dunia.''',
        bodyEn: '''After the Pandavas\' thirteen years of exile ended, Duryodhana refused to return even five small villages as a peaceful compromise, insisting he would not surrender land the size of a needle\'s point without war. Krishna himself traveled as a peace envoy to Hastinapura, pleading for peace to avoid bloodshed between kin, but was flatly refused and nearly seized by the enraged Duryodhana. With every peaceful path exhausted, both sides gathered allies from across Bharatavarsha; the Kauravas assembled eleven divisions of troops (akshauhini), while the Pandavas had only seven, though strengthened by Krishna\'s presence as advisor and Arjuna\'s charioteer. The two armies finally camped facing one another on the plain of Kurukshetra, a sacred ground chosen for its neutrality, on the eve of an eighteen-day war that would shake the entire world.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Hari-Hari Awal: Kejatuhan Bhishma',
        headingEn: 'Early Days: The Fall of Bhishma',
        body: '''Bhishma, kakek agung dari kedua belah pihak yang telah bersumpah membujang demi ayahnya, terpaksa memimpin pasukan Korawa karena kesetiaannya pada takhta Hastinapura, meski hatinya condong kepada Pandawa. Selama sepuluh hari pertama, kesaktiannya nyaris tak tertandingi, membantai ribuan prajurit Pandawa setiap harinya. Para Pandawa akhirnya mencari cara menaklukkannya dan mengetahui rahasia Bhishma: ia bersumpah tak akan mengangkat senjata melawan Shikhandi, yang di kehidupan sebelumnya terlahir sebagai perempuan bernama Amba yang dendam kepadanya. Pada hari kesepuluh, Arjuna menempatkan Shikhandi di depan keretanya; Bhishma menurunkan senjatanya, dan pada saat itulah Arjuna melepaskan hujan anak panah yang menembus tubuhnya dari segala arah. Bhishma roboh, tubuhnya tertopang oleh ratusan anak panah bagai ranjang, namun berkat anugerah memilih waktu kematiannya sendiri, ia bertahan hidup hingga perang usai sebelum akhirnya wafat.''',
        bodyEn: '''Bhishma, the venerable grandsire of both sides who had sworn celibacy for his father\'s sake, was compelled to lead the Kaurava army out of loyalty to the throne of Hastinapura, even though his heart leaned toward the Pandavas. For the first ten days, his prowess was nearly unmatched, slaughtering thousands of Pandava soldiers each day. The Pandavas eventually sought a way to overcome him and learned Bhishma\'s secret: he had vowed never to raise arms against Shikhandi, who in a former life had been born a woman named Amba who bore a grudge against him. On the tenth day, Arjuna placed Shikhandi before his chariot; Bhishma lowered his weapon, and at that moment Arjuna released a hail of arrows that pierced his body from every side. Bhishma collapsed, his body supported by hundreds of arrows like a bed, but thanks to the boon of choosing the moment of his own death, he lingered until the war\'s end before finally passing away.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Drona Menjadi Panglima',
        headingEn: 'Drona Becomes Commander',
        body: '''Setelah kejatuhan Bhishma, Guru Drona, mantan pengajar memanah kedua belah pihak, mengambil alih komando Korawa. Ia menyusun formasi labirin Chakravyuha yang mematikan; hanya sedikit yang tahu cara masuk, dan lebih sedikit lagi yang tahu cara keluar. Abhimanyu, putra Arjuna yang gagah berani dan hanya mengetahui cara menembus formasi itu tanpa tahu cara kembali, nekat menyerbu sendirian ketika ayahnya sedang bertempur di medan lain. Ia bertempur luar biasa gagah sebelum akhirnya dikepung dan dibunuh secara curang oleh enam maharathi Korawa sekaligus, melanggar aturan perang ksatria. Murka atas kematian putranya, Arjuna bersumpah akan membunuh Jayadratha, raja yang menghalangi bala bantuan mencapai Abhimanyu, sebelum matahari terbenam esok hari, sebuah sumpah yang akhirnya dipenuhi berkat tipu daya Krishna yang menciptakan gerhana matahari semu. Drona sendiri kemudian gugur ketika Dhrishtadyumna memenggalnya saat ia meletakkan senjata karena disesatkan kabar bohong kematian putranya, Ashwatthama.''',
        bodyEn: '''After Bhishma\'s fall, Guru Drona, the former archery teacher of both sides, took command of the Kauravas. He arranged the deadly Chakravyuha labyrinth formation; few knew how to enter it, and fewer still knew how to escape. Abhimanyu, Arjuna\'s valiant son, who knew only how to breach the formation but not how to exit, boldly charged in alone while his father was fighting elsewhere. He fought magnificently before finally being surrounded and unfairly killed by six Kaurava maharathis at once, violating the rules of chivalrous warfare. Enraged by his son\'s death, Arjuna vowed to kill Jayadratha, the king who had blocked reinforcements from reaching Abhimanyu, before sunset the next day, a vow ultimately fulfilled thanks to Krishna\'s trick of creating an illusory solar eclipse. Drona himself later fell when Dhrishtadyumna beheaded him as he laid down his weapons, deceived by a false report of the death of his son, Ashwatthama.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Karna Sang Panglima Tragis',
        headingEn: 'Karna, the Tragic Commander',
        body: '''Setelah Drona gugur, Karna diangkat menjadi panglima Korawa. Karna sesungguhnya adalah putra sulung Kunti dari Dewa Surya, yang dibuang saat bayi dan dibesarkan oleh keluarga kusir, sehingga secara darah ia adalah kakak tertua para Pandawa, sebuah rahasia yang baru diungkap Krishna dan Kunti menjelang perang. Meski demikian, Karna tetap setia kepada sahabatnya Duryodhana yang selama ini menghormatinya meski rendah kastanya. Dibebani kutukan gurunya Parashurama dan seorang Brahmana yang membuatnya lupa ilmu penting, serta baju zirah saktinya yang telah diserahkan kepada Indra demi kehormatan, Karna maju bertarung melawan Arjuna dengan segala kelemahan itu. Di tengah duel sengit, roda kereta Karna terjebak dalam lumpur; ketika ia turun untuk membebaskannya sambil meminta jeda sesuai aturan perang, Krishna mendesak Arjuna untuk tetap menyerang, mengingatkan segala ketidakadilan yang pernah dilakukan Korawa. Arjuna pun melepaskan panah yang memenggal kepala Karna, mengakhiri hidup salah satu pahlawan paling tragis dalam epos ini.''',
        bodyEn: '''After Drona fell, Karna was made commander of the Kauravas. Karna was, in truth, Kunti\'s eldest son by the Sun God Surya, abandoned as an infant and raised by a charioteer\'s family, making him, by blood, the eldest of the Pandava brothers, a secret revealed only by Krishna and Kunti shortly before the war. Even so, Karna remained loyal to his friend Duryodhana, who had honored him despite his low birth. Burdened by curses from his teachers Parashurama and a Brahmin that made him forget crucial knowledge at the critical moment, and having already surrendered his magical armor to Indra for the sake of honor, Karna went into battle against Arjuna carrying all these disadvantages. In the fierce duel, Karna\'s chariot wheel became stuck in the mud; as he climbed down to free it while requesting a pause under the rules of war, Krishna urged Arjuna to keep attacking, reminding him of every injustice the Kauravas had committed. Arjuna then loosed the arrow that beheaded Karna, ending the life of one of the epic\'s most tragic heroes.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Kejatuhan Duryodhana dan Akhir Perang',
        headingEn: 'The Fall of Duryodhana and the End of War',
        body: '''Dengan gugurnya Karna, semangat pasukan Korawa runtuh dan satu demi satu panglima mereka tumbang. Setelah delapan belas hari pertempuran, hampir seluruh laki-laki dari kedua belah pihak tewas, menyisakan sedikit yang selamat. Duryodhana yang terluka dan putus asa melarikan diri, bersembunyi di dasar sebuah telaga menggunakan ilmu menyelam gaib. Ditemukan oleh Pandawa, ia dipaksa keluar dan setuju menghadapi duel gada melawan siapa pun yang dipilih musuhnya; Bima maju sebagai penantang. Pertarungan berlangsung sengit hingga Krishna mengingatkan Bima akan sumpah lamanya di balairung dahulu. Bima pun melanggar aturan duel gada dengan memukul paha Duryodhana hingga remuk, jatuh sekarat. Malam itu juga, Ashwatthama, putra Drona yang dendam, menyusup ke perkemahan Pandawa saat mereka tak berjaga dan membantai hampir seluruh pasukan yang tersisa, termasuk kelima putra Draupadi, dalam serangan gelap yang mengerikan dan melanggar semua etika perang.''',
        bodyEn: '''With Karna\'s death, the Kaurava army\'s spirit collapsed, and their commanders fell one after another. After eighteen days of fighting, nearly every man on both sides lay dead, leaving only a handful of survivors. The wounded and desperate Duryodhana fled and hid at the bottom of a lake using a mystic power of submersion. Found by the Pandavas, he was forced out and agreed to face a mace duel against whichever opponent they chose; Bhima stepped forward as challenger. The fight raged fiercely until Krishna reminded Bhima of his old vow made in the assembly hall years before. Bhima then broke the rules of mace combat by striking Duryodhana\'s thigh, shattering it and leaving him dying. That very night, Ashwatthama, Drona\'s vengeful son, crept into the unguarded Pandava camp and slaughtered nearly all the remaining troops, including Draupadi\'s five sons, in a horrifying night raid that violated every code of war.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Penutup: Duka dan Penobatan Yudhishthira',
        headingEn: 'Closing: Mourning and Yudhishthira\'s Coronation',
        body: '''Perang Kurukshetra berakhir dengan kemenangan Pandawa, namun kemenangan itu terasa hampa dan penuh duka. Hampir seluruh generasi ksatria Bharatavarsha telah musnah; Gandhari, ibu Duryodhana yang telah kehilangan seratus putranya, meratap pilu dan mengutuk Krishna atas kehancuran itu, meramalkan bahwa dinasti Yadu Krishna sendiri kelak akan binasa dengan cara serupa. Yudhishthira, dilanda rasa bersalah mendalam atas jutaan nyawa yang hilang, sempat ingin melepaskan takhta dan hidup sebagai petapa, namun dinasihati para tetua dan Krishna tentang tanggung jawab seorang raja untuk memulihkan tatanan meski hatinya berduka. Ia akhirnya dinobatkan sebagai raja Hastinapura, memerintah dengan bijaksana selama bertahun-tahun sebelum akhirnya menyerahkan takhta dan berjalan menuju pegunungan Himalaya bersama saudara-saudaranya, mengakhiri kisah panjang Mahabharata dengan renungan mendalam tentang harga kemenangan yang dibeli dengan kehancuran hampir seluruh dunia yang mereka kenal.''',
        bodyEn: '''The Kurukshetra War ended in Pandava victory, yet the triumph felt hollow and full of grief. Nearly an entire generation of Bharatavarsha\'s warriors had perished; Gandhari, Duryodhana\'s mother, who had lost all hundred of her sons, wept bitterly and cursed Krishna for the devastation, foretelling that his own Yadu dynasty would one day perish in a similarly tragic manner. Yudhishthira, burdened with deep guilt over the millions of lives lost, briefly wished to renounce the throne and live as an ascetic, but was counseled by the elders and Krishna on a king\'s responsibility to restore order despite a grieving heart. He was finally crowned king of Hastinapura, ruling wisely for many years before eventually relinquishing the throne and journeying toward the Himalayas with his brothers, closing the long tale of the Mahabharata with a profound meditation on the cost of a victory bought with the destruction of nearly the entire world they had known.''',
      ),
