    impact: '''Perang Kurukshetra memusnahkan hampir seluruh generasi ksatria Bharatavarsha dan mengakhiri dinasti Korawa sepenuhnya. Yudhishthira naik takhta sebagai raja Hastinapura, namun harus menanggung beban moral atas kehancuran besar itu sepanjang hidupnya. Kutukan Gandhari kepada Krishna kelak terwujud dalam kehancuran dinasti Yadu. Perang ini menjadi peristiwa penentu yang menutup zaman Dvapara dan membuka jalan menuju Kaliyuga, era kemerosotan moral, menjadikannya batas waktu paling penting dalam kosmologi Hindu tentang siklus zaman dunia.''',
    impactEn: '''The Kurukshetra War annihilated nearly an entire generation of Bharatavarsha\'s warriors and completely ended the Kaurava dynasty. Yudhishthira ascended the throne of Hastinapura but carried the moral weight of that immense destruction for the rest of his life. Gandhari\'s curse upon Krishna would later be fulfilled in the destruction of his own Yadu dynasty. The war stands as the defining event that closes the Dvapara Yuga and opens the path to the Kali Yuga, the age of moral decline, making it the most significant time marker in Hindu cosmology\'s cycle of ages.''',
    meaning: '''Perang Kurukshetra menggambarkan bahwa perang dharma, meski dibenarkan, tetap membawa duka dan kehilangan yang tak terhindarkan bagi semua pihak, bukan hanya yang kalah. Kematian para pahlawan besar seperti Bhishma, Drona, dan Karna, masing-masing terikat konflik batin antara kesetiaan dan kebenaran, menunjukkan kompleksitas moral dharma yang tak pernah hitam-putih. Kemenangan yang diraih dengan kecurangan taktis, seperti kematian Drona dan Karna, mengingatkan bahwa bahkan pihak yang benar dapat tergoda melanggar aturan demi tujuan yang mereka yakini adil.''',
    meaningEn: '''The Kurukshetra War shows that even a righteous war, though justified, brings inevitable grief and loss to all sides, not only the defeated. The deaths of great heroes such as Bhishma, Drona, and Karna, each bound by an inner conflict between loyalty and truth, reveal the moral complexity of dharma, which is never simply black and white. Victories achieved through tactical deception, such as the deaths of Drona and Karna, remind us that even the righteous side can be tempted to break the rules for a cause they believe just.''',
  ),
];
